{
  "id": "q-sep6-sep24-sep31-choice",
  "question": "When should an integration use SEP-6, SEP-24, or SEP-31 for fiat on/off-ramp and cross-border flows?",
  "surface": [
    "stellarDocs.search_anchor_sep_docs",
    "scout.searchResearch",
    "skills.stellar-dev.standards"
  ],
  "golden": {
    "answer": "As of 2026-07-11, SEP-6, SEP-24, and SEP-31 are Active. Use SEP-24 for an anchor-hosted interactive deposit/withdrawal UI; use SEP-6 for programmatic deposit/withdrawal—the legacy interactive SEP-6 flow is deprecated in favor of SEP-24, not the whole SEP. For SEP-31, a Sending Anchor calls a Receiving Anchor under an established bilateral or commercial relationship for cross-border payout. Discover them through SEP-1 keys TRANSFER_SERVER, TRANSFER_SERVER_SEP0024, and DIRECT_PAYMENT_SERVER respectively. Add SEP-38 when quotes or rates are part of the corridor.",
    "keyFacts": [
      "SEP-24 is the anchor-hosted interactive deposit/withdrawal flow; SEP-6 is the programmatic deposit/withdrawal API.",
      "SEP-6 remains Active; its legacy interactive flow, not the whole SEP, is deprecated in favor of SEP-24.",
      "SEP-31 has a Sending Anchor call a Receiving Anchor under an established bilateral/commercial relationship.",
      "SEP-6, SEP-24, SEP-31, and SEP-38 were Active as of 2026-07-11; SEP-38 applies when quotes/rates are part of the corridor.",
      "SEP-1 keys TRANSFER_SERVER, TRANSFER_SERVER_SEP0024, and DIRECT_PAYMENT_SERVER distinguish the endpoints."
    ],
    "avoid": [
      "SEP-31 is simply the newest replacement for both SEP-6 and SEP-24.",
      "SEP-24 requires the wallet to collect and host the anchor's KYC user interface."
    ]
  },
